==Translingual==

===Symbol===

'''ƒ'''

# The letter '''{{unicode|Ƒ}}''' (minuscule: '''ƒ''') is a letter of the [[Latin]] [[alphabet]], based on the [[italic]] form of [[F]]. It is used in writing the [[Ewe]] [[language]] to represent a voiceless bilabial fricative ({{IPA|/ɸ/}}), as distinct from the letter [[F]], which represents a voiceless labiodental fricative. Compare {{unicode|[[Ʋ]]}}, which is the equivalent voiced sound.

#: The minuscule '''ƒ''' is also used as an abbreviation for the currencies [[florin]], and formerly [[gulden]] and [[guilder]].

